quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  33,1,"O Prophet, be mindful of Allah and do not obey the deniers and the hypocrites. Indeed, Allah has always been All-Knowing, All-Wise."
  33,2,"And follow what is revealed to yousg from your Lord; indeed, Allah has always been All-Aware of what youpl do1 ."
  33,3,"And place yoursg trust in Allah, for Allah is sufficient as a Trustee."
  33,4,"Never did Allah make two hearts inside any man’s body, nor did He ever make yourpl spouses whom you reject and compare to your mothers’ backs into your actual mothers. Nor did He make your adopted sons your actual sons. That is your saying coming out of your mouths, and Allah speaks the truth and He guides to the way."
  33,5,"Call them after their fathers; that is more equitable with Allah. But if youpl do not know their fathers, then your brethren in faith and your protégés. And you commit no sin if you err therein, except for what your hearts premeditate. And Allah has always been Oft-Forgiving, Bestowing of mercy."
  33,6,"The Prophet is worthier as a guardian of the believers than they are of themselves, and his spouses are(as) mothers to them. And blood relatives are worthier than the(other) believers or the immigrants1as heirs of one another according to Allah’s Scripture—except that youpl may do an upright act to your allies; that has been inscribed in the Scripture."